{
  "text": "An excellent technique for enumerating fecal bacterial species without culture, by using species-specific DNA hybridization probes, was recently reported by Kuritza et al. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, the application of their method to any of the intestinal bacteria is limited because of its sensitivity, as they stated [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The identification method described here seems to be one of the most convenient methods now.",
